reviews.review_text: THE FALL TOUR IS KILLER AS WELL I THINK ALOT OF PEOPLE FORGET ABOUT THE FALL OF '77 AND CONCENTRATE ON THE SPRING>SUMMER.THIS SHOW IS ONE THAT IS FORGOTTEN ALONG WITH R.P.I AND SENECA COLLEGE,ROCHESTER,AND I THINK BROOME COUNTY IS AS ENERGETIC AS ANYTHING IN '77. THESE GUY'S WERE JUST LOVIN' LIFE AND IT SHOW'S EACH NIGHT.JUST LISTEN TO PHIL PLAYING SLIDE BASS,AND GARCIA WELL WHAT ELSE CAN BE SAID 4 HIM,AS WELL AS ACE LAYING DONE THOSE KILLER CHORDS.I COULD GO ON MUCH LONGER BUT IT HAS ALL BEEN SAID.''ONE LONG RIDE FROM START TO END GONNA'TAKE THAT RIDE AGAIN''.IF WE ONLY COULD. PEACE...........

What he said Broome county IS as energetic as any '77, and as for Seneca...Had that on casette for years and lost it. Looking for an aud of it; again for the energy. Sick 2nd set. Every night was packed with
explosivness. Songs that became passive as time went by, need to be listened to during this period (as I listen to a crancking Brown Eyed).
These were the days!!!!
Very grainy, cloudy, patchy sound. Great show, but there are better copies.
